Learn more about who we are and what we do at the Dade City Woman's Club.
Our Mission
To provide a means whereby an individual may be of service to our community through active participation in programs benefiting education, assisting those less fortunate through other charitable purposes and continuing to preserve the historical significance of the Dade City Woman's Club building.
Read more
Why Choose the Dade City Woman's Club?
WHO are the members of the Dade City Womanâs Club and what do they do?
The club is made up of community-minded women of all ages from the Dade City area and beyond, who have joined together to provide community service through volunteering and fundraising.
WHAT are the benefits of membership?
The benefit is the satisfaction of being part of a local service organization that âmakes a differenceâ in our community.
Being a member provides the opportunity to meet other women who share your interests and concerns, and of course build friendships. Members are encouraged to support the clubâs fundraising projects and urged to participate in volunteer service activities.

Interested in becoming a DCWC Member?
Please see the read more section above in Why Choose the Dade City Woman's Club for a membership application. The club has a general business meeting on the 3rd Thursday of each month at 6:00 p.m., at the club located at 37922 Palm Avenue, Dade City, FL
33525. Please
contact
